Czech Stocks: Central European Media, New World Resources Move

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-24T12:16:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/czech-stocks-central-european-media-new-world-resources-move.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
rose 0.4 percent to 1,003.1 as of 1:52 p.m. in  Prague , reducing
its drop this month to 15 percent.  The following are among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV)   rose 5.4
percent to 212.9 koruna, heading for its biggest one-day advance
in four weeks. Chief Financial Officer David Sach bought 20,000
company shares last week, the broadcaster part-owned by Time
Warner Inc., said in a regulatory filing yesterday.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the largest Czech coking-
coal producer, rose 1.3 percent to 160 koruna, reducing this
month’s decline to 29 percent. NWR earlier today jumped as much
as 4.4 percent after the company published a second-quarter
profit that exceeded analyst estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  